{
  "stem": "11274.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They were from Lwow, I think-- and for the whole summer-- and they paid me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I had the food there in the hotel, and everything-- the hotel room.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the baby was sleeping in the same room with me so the parents could go out late at night.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Go out to concerts, whatever was available there for them-- and dances.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Then I took care of the little boy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And then for two summers I did this.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And then later on, I found out-- I was studying sewing while my sister Zosia was a dressmaker, by the way, when she [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I started about the war talking, but I should have told you before.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "When she was married she was still doing some-- a little bit, dressmaking.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But before she got married, she had-- she was a dressmaking making business in our house.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We extended one room extra for her.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And then she married.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "She still was doing a little bit.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I learned to sew from her, from my sister.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And then-- and Danka learned to sew from her a little bit, too.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So both of us knew a little bit how to sew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "So I went to Krynica, and I went into a store that was selling Tiroler from Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "In Tyrol they make embroidered things on felt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And you have to put them together.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So-- so parts of a skirt with decorated straps, or jackets with some-- under lapel-- some decoration-- embroidery, hand embroidery.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "So I went in a store and asked if I could have a job there, and yes, they hired me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And in the Jewish hotel again because I was eating there, too, and sleeping there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So for several weeks during the summer, and sometimes-- one summer I did the whole summer there.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
